{
  "texts": [
    "Studies, however, have shown that nodule microenvironments such as fibrosis may play a role in lung cancer malignancy.",
    "Karampitsakos et al. and Li et al.",
    "found that pulmonary fibrosis increases a patient's risk of developing lung cancer.",
    "Salvatore et al.",
    "revealed that pulmonary fibrosis is observed in 6.6% of lung cancer screening participants compared to 0.03% among men and 0.02% among women of the general public [5][6][7]."
  ]
}